Package quicktag.data

Class Data

java.lang.Object
quicktag.data.Data
public class Data
extends java.lang.Object
Data contains the variables that handle and store the html/css information.

    • getContent

      public java.lang.String getContent()
      Gets the "content" variable, which stores all the HTML data.
      Returns:

    • setContent

      public void setContent​(java.lang.String content)
      Appends new data to the "content" variable.
      Parameters:
      content - The variable that stores all HTML data

    • clearContent

      public void clearContent()
      Clears all data stored in the "content" variable. Used at the end of write methods so that data does not carry over to new html pages.

    • getStyling

      public java.lang.String getStyling()
      Gets the "styling" variable, which stores all the CSS data.
      Returns:
      styling

    • setStyling

      public void setStyling​(java.lang.String styling)
      Appends new data to the "styling" variable.
      Parameters:
      styling - The variable that stores all CSS data

    • clearStyling

      public void clearStyling()
      Clears all data stored in the "styling" variable. Used at the end of write methods so that data does not carry over to new css pages.

    • generateId

      public java.lang.String generateId()
      All the Basic HTML elements that are not given an ID by the user, will call on this method to generate a new ID automatically in this format: obj1, obj2, obj3, obj4 ...
      Returns:
      A generated id for HTML elements

    • getGeneratedId

      public java.lang.String getGeneratedId()
      Gets the most recently generated ID. Used by the Style method "css" to style elements that were not given an ID by the user.
      Returns:
      The most recently generated ID

    • getHtmlTitle

      public java.lang.String getHtmlTitle()
      Gets the current title of the HTML page.
      Returns:
      htmlTitle

    • setHtmlTitle

      public void setHtmlTitle​(java.lang.String htmlTitle)
      Sets the title of the HTML page that will be used by the Write methods.
      Parameters:
      htmlTitle - The current title

    • getCurrentContainer

      public java.lang.String getCurrentContainer()
      Gets the current most recently opened container type. The "close" method in Container will use this to close the most recently opened container.
      Returns:
      currentContainer

    • setCurrentContainer

      public void setCurrentContainer​(java.lang.String container)
      Used by the Container methods, as they will set currentContainer to be their own container type. (i.e the "div" method will set the currentContainer type to "div".)
      Parameters:
      container - The type of the most recent container

    • clearCurrentContainer

      public void clearCurrentContainer()
      Clears the current container type when a container is closed.
